    "history" -> {"14,1", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "QuantumMob/Q3",
     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "GottesmanMap[mat] represents the Clifford operator corresponding to the \
Gottesman matrix mat, and is to operate on a Gottesman vector or a matrix \
consisting of rows of Gottesman vectors. GottesmanMap[mat, {k1, k2, ...}] \
represents the Clifford operator that is non-trivial only on qubits numbered \
k1, k2, ..., and is to operate on any number of qubits (larger than every \
ki). GottesmanMap[spec][v] returns Gottesman vector w such that P[w] = \
C[spec] ** P[v] ** Dagger[C[spec]], where P[v] and C[spec] refer to the Pauli \
string and Clifford operator corresponding to Gottesman vector v and \
specification spec (see above), respectively. GottesmanMap[spec][{v1, v2, \
...}] automatically maps each vk and returns the result in a matrix form.", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "GottesmanMap", 
    "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> 
    "GottesmanMap", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/GottesmanMap"}},
